The ODM chief said the illiterate electorate are already overburdened by six ballot papers.In a message likely to shut the door on the DP over his continued call for a multiple-choice referendum, Mr Odinga said the process is now headed for a 'Yes' or 'No' vote. ODM leader Raila Odinga has likened the proposal by Deputy President William Ruto for a multiple-choice referendum to subjecting Kenyans to a confusing school examination.
Mr Odinga also fired a warning shot at organisations which he claimed have been going round trying to sway county assemblies to reject the Constitutional Amendment Bill 2020 when it is tabled before the various Houses.



