Speaking separately in Kisumu and Vihiga yesterday, the ODM chief said the illiterate electorate are already overburdened by six ballot papers.
He said it would be unfair to add not just a seventh one but 10 or more questions on parts of the referendum that they agree with or oppose. “It is like sending someone to an examination. Even for someone who has been in school for 12 years, it will be a challenge and now you are asking an illiterate person to do that on the same day there is a general election,” said Mr Odinga.



