Shut the door
In a message likely to shut the door on the DP over his continued call for a multiple-choice referendum, Mr Odinga said the process is now headed for a 'Yes' or 'No' vote.
“That is an individual who wants to say no, but doesn’t have the strength of character to say I oppose. He is pretending and basically trying to hold the country back,” said Mr Odinga after he met Kisumu Governor Anyang’ Nyong’o and his Kakamega counterpart Wycliffe Oparanya.
Speaking in Musalia Mudavadi's Vihiga home turf, Mr Odinga stressed the point further, saying Dr Ruto is opposed to the Building Bridges Initiative (BBI) and is only bringing up the issue of a multiple-choice referendum to derailing the process.



