Mr Odinga was attending the burial of Timothy Amiani, 78, at Kegondi in Sabatia. The deceased was the father of Busia Woman Representative Florence Mutua, who is also the ODM assistant secretary-general.
Read: Ruto camp’s new strategy on referendum question
Mr Odinga sensationally claimed the said organisations are ‘poisoning’ the minds of ward reps so that they shoot down the BBI Bill when it is brought to them early next year. “I want to tell the organisations that they are engaging in a futile process,” said Mr Odinga.
Revenue generation
Kakamega Governor Wycliffe Oparanya urged the proponents of the multiple-choice vote to lead the "No camp".
The Council of Governors chairman called on healthcare workers who are on strike to return to work. "Due to Covid-19, revenue generation has gone down and this is a new normal," he said.
Mr Oparanya said he will be at the Senate today to push for a solution to the health crisis.
